metadata.name: Inattendu #239
metadata.description:
"Inattendu" is a nod to my previous project "VoilÃ " which produced some unexpected output because of a bug happening with Brave browser shield.
Simple things are often the best...
It seemed like people (and I) really liked these results, so I'm making them available for free as a new project.

The recursive algorithm is the same as the one used with "VoilÃ ", but the shapes are fully painted, it produces those interesting views.

Reserves for the people who minted my previous project "VoilÃ " ðŸ’—

Press 's' to save a high res PNG:
- Square format: 2508x2508
- Portrait & Landscape format: 3128x2018

Made with p5js. France, April 2023, Nicazo.

metadata.name: YYYSEED #956
metadata.description:
ðŸ”¥ BURN NOTICE: This is a FIVE DAY "open edition" to celebrate the launch of fx(params). The project is open for minting from the start of Monday until midnight Friday (GMT).

YYYSEED is an artwork with an aesthetic that works across digital, print and pen plotting mediums, leaning towards the minimalistic nature of drawing machines. SVGs can be exported for this purpose.

I've designed the algorithm to work best for this with the default settings, you should be good to go right out of the box. You can explore the design space a little further using the parameters (more details below).

If you're planning on plotting the work at larger sizes (A2, A1), then the "Override suggest lines" is there for you to cram more of them into the extra space.

PARAMS ::::::::::::::

The initial settings of the parameters are what I think best for the look I'm trying to achieve as the artist: minimal pen plotting work. This comes from the "Suggested" and "Random for hash" values.

You can take the design away from that by turning the "Use suggested lines" and "Use suggested destroyer" options off, and using your own values with the slider.

"Random for hash" means the feature has been randomly selected and fixed for the current hash and won't change. For example, if the hash is 'ooABCD' and the grid's "Random for hash" picks 3x4, then it will always be 3x4 for that hash, it isn't random each time you change sometime. Picking a new hash however will then randomly pick a new (fixed) option.

DANGER SEED :::::::::

USE OF THE DANGER SEED IS NOT RECOMMENDED. If you set the DANGER SEED, the value will be encoded along with the rest of the params (where it can be decoded) in the stored data of the mint, along with the token.

The DANGER SEED will only take effect if it starts with 'YYY', it will STOMP all over the other settings, including the hash.

INSTRUCTIONS ::::::::

h - Toggle highres mode on/off (starts off)
t - Toggle paper background on/off
s - Save png (in highres if toggled on)
1-6 - Save SVGs for plotting A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, A6

PEN PLOTTING ::::::::

Press 1-6 to select which A1-6 size paper you want to plot onto, the the system will download one or more files for you to use, one file per colour.

Please tag #plottertwitter, or #penplotter on twitter, instagram & mastodon

PRINTING ::::::::::::

The output of the high resolution version is 6,144 x 8,192 pixels. That will print at the following sizes.

300dpi: 20.48 x 27.31 inches (52.02 x 69.35 cm)
200dpi: 30.72 x 40.96 inches (78.03 x 104.03 cm)

300dpi is recommended, but 200dpi should be fine for this design. I suggest turning the paper texture off if you're printing onto textured archival paper, you can leave it on when printing onto smooth white paper.

metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #267
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition â€˜Organic Matrâ€™ (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


â€”â€” 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minterâ€™s wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a â€˜scaleâ€™ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.

@uvdsc, 2022

metadata.name: Canevach #334
metadata.description:
Canevach started as a code golfing experiment, 280 characters of HTML, CSS and JavaScript producing pixelated patterns when copy-pasted in the address bar of a web browser.

The code has been adapted for the sake of entropy control and readability, but I tried to keep it as lean as possible to honour the code golfing spirit that initiated the project.

The artwork is generated by manipulating pixels directly through the Canvas API.

Colours are uniformly selected in RGB space, without any colour theory considerations. The only exception is for black, which is made more prominent by the way the algorithm is initiated.

Features
â€¢ Canvas size: 8x8 | 16x16 | 32x32 | 64x64 | 128x128
â€¢ Number of colours: 1 to 5

fx(hash) Generative Token by loackme

metadata.name: Cosmo Fibrils #118
metadata.description:
As a child browsing through an encyclopedia (Tout l'Univers), I stumbled upon a printed photograph of a nebulae. It felt so familiar although I couldn't have ever seen one before. I felt projected into a vibrant novel universe. To this day, this rhapsodic experience remains deeply imprinted in me. This piece is my expression for its nostalgia.

The drawing has been slowed down on purpose for the viewer to enjoy its fibrous shaping.
Please be patient and relax.

I sincerely hope you will enjoy your lucky token.

Emile Jaaa

metadata.description:
"Trouvaille" is an abstract artwork focusing on the composition and density of elements. Each of the elements are divided and placed according to the algorithm to work in harmony with each other. The background consists of countless lines that create a halo-like state in the center. Various sizes and densities and more than 12 color palettes have been used.

Press â€™sâ€™ on the live mode to save the artwork.

metadata.description:
A collection of runes slowly formulated by 1750 walkers. 
Rarity includes:
One of five random grid sizes
One of ten random festive background colors
One of five fesitve pen colors
1,750 Walkers assigned to a grid space

metadata.name: JUKEBOX #66
metadata.description:
Who has never been possessed by a melody that sticks in their mind? "JukeBox" is a generative series of 450 songs that pay tribute to the tunes that are part of our vital soundtrack. These songs are represented by the international maritime signal flags alphabet. Each letter is a flag and together they give form to the title of a song.
 
Generate the song that you want to dance!
 
Features:
- 450 different song titles.
- Eight different color palettes plus a special pictogram design.
- Each palette represents a rarity according to this list:
* common   (25:100 ratio)
* common+ (20:100 ratio)
* common++ (16:100 ratio)
* uncommon (12:100 ratio)
* uncommon+ (10:100 ratio)
* rare (8:100 ratio)
* ultrarare (6:100 ratio)
* epic (3:100 ratio)

metadata.name: [manic.flow] #2
metadata.description:
a group of squares of varying shapes and sizes queued gently outside of ï½”ï½ˆï½… ï½‡ï½’ï½‰ï½„.
they were then thrown in heedless of their criticisms and concerns and were flung along to points beyond.  those that escaped were forced back into ï½”ï½ˆï½… ï½‡ï½’ï½‰ï½„ to careen against the rushing flow.

some ï½”ï½ˆï½… ï½‡ï½’ï½‰ï½„ are slow, meandering flows.  like condensation dripping off a cold beer bottle.  other ï½”ï½ˆï½… ï½‡ï½’ï½‰ï½„ are fast, frenetic flows. like a water jet blasting away caked-on paint.

only some squares were injured in this ï½”ï½ˆï½… ï½‡ï½’ï½‰ï½„ experiment.  their families were duly compensated.

metadata.name: PATCHES #13
metadata.description:
PATCHES, 2021

This work is based on a series of physical artworks I painted in 2019, entitled "Retalhos". The original artwork was an intimate and introspective representation of the daily tightrope walking feeling between anxiety, uncertainties and momentary happiness, through expressive brushstrokes and balance of cold and warm colors.

These artworks were exhibited in SÃ£o Paulo and were acquired by visitors. That was my first and only  experience selling physical artwork during an actual exhibition.

There are 5 color sets and 4 densities.

You can interact with this generative token:

â€“â€“ Arrows Left & Right
Move

â€“â€“ Arrows Up & Down
Zoom In-Out

â€“â€“ Letters R & T
Rotate entire object

â€“â€“ Letters W & R
Rotate each tile individually

â€“â€“ Letter B
Black background

Have fun taking print of the desirable view and sharing! :)

metadata.name: Wandering Nets Redux #10
metadata.description:
Wandering Nets Redux is a reissue of Wandering Nets (March 2022). Due to an unfortunate error in the original piece Wandering Nets no longer displays live inside the current fxhash UI. This restored and updated generative token is offered free to all collectors of the original, with some additional tweaks and capabilities.

January 2023

Original description as below:

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Wandering Nets is a digital kinetic light sculpture by Matt Ebb.

Networks of light are created and connected via random walks in space and colour. Emergent structures are revealed by the ambient interaction, tension and collision of these networks within themselves and orbiting shadowed spherical bodies.

The piece is the result of several months of custom development in realtime volume rendering. The scene data is generated in javascript and rendered with a bespoke GLSL raytracer - no external libraries are used.

This is a graphically intensive shader. By default it will adaptively adjust sampling quality to target 30fps, though a reasonably fast GPU is recommended for best results.

Mouse drag: Orbit the camera in 3D to explore compositions
[ and ] keys: Override the adaptive samples per pixel lower or higher to trade noise for framerate

March 2022

Update -
spacebar: Disturb the light positions

metadata.name: Fabric Remnants #105
metadata.description:
One of my sisters is a tailor and restorator. This piece is a homage to her. 
Shopping for fabric with her and seeing her atelier while she is working is a 
festival of color, shapes, patterns and a celebration of creativity.

This is my pragmatical take on her work. The fabric like texture and dashed lines
representing the yarn rearranged in a grid of leftovers.

The piece is a generated SVG, because of that it scales easily and is printable.

Use the arrow keys to toggle/tune some things & Space / click to regenerate a new
grid. The P key will toggle auto generation.
